    {
      "id": "sybil_1_listing_1",
      "firm_id": "sybil_1",
      "description": "Hey there! You've seriously gotta see this beauty in person. It\u2019s in absolutely pristine condition\u2014it looks and drives just like it did the day it rolled off the lot! I\u2019ve taken so much pride in keeping it spotless and garage-kept, so it's basically a dream on wheels. If you're looking for something that's been loved and cared for perfectly, this is the one. Feel free to reach out if you have any questions or want to come take a look!",
      "price": 44900.0,
      "reputation": 0.5,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 41
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available for acquisition is a museum-grade 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine with individual throttle bodies and dual-VANOS variable valve timing. This chassis is structurally impeccable, having undergone proactive rear subframe reinforcement and a full cooling system overhaul. The Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox offers crisp engagement, paired with a variable M differential lock for superior lateral traction. The suspension geometry remains true to factory specifications with fresh bushings and dampers, ensuring precise kinematics. Meticulously maintained with a comprehensive service dossier documenting rod bearing replacement and valve adjustments, this specimen represents the pinnacle of naturally aspirated Bavarian engineering.",
      "price": 43500.0,
      "reputation": 0.4,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 41
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_3_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_3",
